'''Lee Jae-sung''' ({{Korean|이재성}}; born 10 August 1992) is a South Korean professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] or [[winger (association football)|winger]] for [[Bundesliga]] club [[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz 05]] and the [[South Korea national football team|South Korea national team]].<ref>{{Soccerway|jae-seong-lee/331232}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Jeonbuk Hyundai Motors===
Lee joined [[Jeonbuk Hyundai Motors]] in 2014 and made his debut in the [[2014 AFC Champions League]] match against [[Yokohama F. Marinos]] on 26 February.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.the-afc.com/en/component/afcasfeeds/?fixtureid=8040&stageid=317&tMode=H&view=ajax&show=matchsummary |title=Match Report - Jeonbuk Hyundai Motors v Yokohama F. Marinos |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140109070618/http://www.the-afc.com/en/component/afcasfeeds/?fixtureid=8040&stageid=317&tMode=H&view=ajax&show=matchsummary |archive-date=9 January 2014 |publisher=AFC}}</ref> [[Choi Kang-hee (footballer)|Choi Kang-hee]], the manager of Jeonbuk at the time, praised his ability which kept balance about attack and defense of team, and actively used him, the newcomer.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.news1.kr/articles/?2142412 |script-title=ko:최강희 감독은 1년 전 이틀 만에 이재성을 알았다 |publisher=News1 |language=ko |date=18 March 2015 |access-date=9 June 2020}}</ref>

In 2016, he spent his best season by providing 17 assists during a year and winning the [[2016 AFC Champions League]].<ref name="kleague"/>

In the [[2017 K League Classic|2017 K League 1]], he won the [[K League MVP Award|Most Valuable Player]] award after having eight goals and ten assists during 28 appearances.<ref name="kleague"/><ref name="17KLeague"/>

===Holstein Kiel===
In July 2018, Lee joined [[2. Bundesliga]] club [[Holstein Kiel]] on a three-year deal until 30 June 2021.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Geidel |first1=Andreas |title=Transfer-Hammer: Jea-Song Lee und Jonas Meffert zu Holstein Kiel |url=http://www.sportbuzzer.de/artikel/transfer-hammer-jea-song-lee-und-jonas-meffert-zu-holstein-kiel/ |access-date=29 July 2018 |publisher=Sportbuzzer |date=27 July 2018 |language=de |archive-date=11 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221011113440/https://www.sportbuzzer.de/artikel/transfer-hammer-jea-song-lee-und-jonas-meffert-zu-holstein-kiel/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> The transfer fee paid to Jeonbuk was reported as €1.5 million.<ref>{{cite news |title=Holstein Kiel verpflichtet Jae-Song Lee |url=http://www.fr.de/sport/fussball-bundesliga/zweitebundesliga/fussball-holstein-kiel-verpflichtet-jae-song-lee-a-1552756 |access-date=29 July 2018 |publisher=Frankfurter Rundschau |date=27 July 2018 |language=de}}</ref> He played his first game against [[Hamburger SV]] on 4 August, and was named the player of the matchday by leaving a deep impression on ''[[Kicker (sports magazine)|kicker]]'' with two assists.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.kicker.de/2-bundesliga/elf-des-tages/2018-19/1 |title=2. Bundesliga Elf des Tages - 2018/19 - 1. Spieltag |publisher=kicker |language=de |access-date=9 June 2020}}</ref>

After the end of the [[2019–20 2. Bundesliga|2019–20 season]], his goal against [[Karlsruher SC]] was selected as Kiel's Goal of the Season.<ref name="tds">{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/Holstein_Kiel/status/1291062889953013763 |title=Lee hat das KSV-"Tor der Saison" 2019/20 geschossen! |language=de |website=Twitter.com |publisher=Holstein Kiel |date=6 August 2020 |access-date=6 August 2020}}</ref>

On 13 January 2021, he played full time and scored the fourth penalty in a [[2020–21 DFB-Pokal]] match, where Kiel won 6–5 on penalties after drawing 2–2 against [[Bayern Munich]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.kicker.de/kiel-gegen-bayern-2021-dfb-pokal-4690551/schema |title=DFB-Pokal - Schema - Holstein Kiel 6:5 Bayern München |access-date=7 July 2021 |publisher=kicker |language=de}}</ref> Afterwards, Kiel reached the semi-finals of DFB-Pokal for the first time in history, but they were eliminated by [[Borussia Dortmund]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.kicker.de/dortmund-gegen-kiel-2021-dfb-pokal-4702976/analyse |title=Kiel geht unter: Dortmund steht nach historischer Halbzeit im Pokalfinale |date=1 May 2021 |access-date=7 July 2021 |publisher=kicker |language=de}}</ref>

Kiel also finished third in the [[2020–21 2. Bundesliga]], qualifying for the promotion play-off. In the two-legged play-off, Lee scored a goal and provided an assist, contributing to all two of Kiel's goals, but they lost 5–2 on aggregate to [[1. FC Köln|Köln]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.kicker.de/koeln-gegen-kiel-2021-bundesliga-relegation-4704508/analyse |title=Joker Lorenz schockt Köln und hat Aufstieg im Visier |date=26 May 2021 |access-date=7 July 2021 |publisher=kicker |language=de}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.kicker.de/kiel-gegen-koeln-2021-bundesliga-relegation-4704509/analyse |title=Andersson macht's früh klar: Köln hält die Klasse |date=29 May 2021 |access-date=7 July 2021 |publisher=kicker |language=de}}</ref>

===Mainz 05===
In July 2021, Lee joined [[Bundesliga]] club [[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz 05]] on a three-year deal until 30 June 2024.<ref>{{cite web |title=05er Verpflichten Jae-sung Lee |url=https://www.mainz05.de/news/05er-verpflichten-jae-sung-lee/ |website=Mainz 05|access-date=8 July 2021 |language=de |date=8 July 2021}}</ref>

Lee was named the player of the 22nd matchday by ''kicker'' after dominating [[Borussia Mönchengladbach]] including a goal and an assist on 24 February 2023.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.kicker.de/bundesliga/elf-des-tages/2022-23/22 |title=Bundesliga - Elf des Tages - 2022/23 - 22. Spieltag |language=de |publisher=kicker |access-date=2023-03-09}}</ref> In that month, he was nominated for the Bundesliga Player of the Month by leading Mainz to three Bundesliga victories as well as having three goals and two assists,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/player-of-the-month-2022-23-ea-sports-fifa-bayern-dortmund-leipzig-22582 |title=Raphael Guerreiro, Julian Brandt, Nico Schlotterbeck, Jae-sung Lee, Borna Sosa and Alphonso Davies nominated for February Player of the Month |publisher=Bundesliga |date=2023-03-09 |access-date=2023-03-09}}</ref> but lost to [[Julian Brandt]]. He was also nominated for the Bundesliga Team of the Season because of his steady performance during the 2022–23 season, but failed to be selected.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://onefootball.com/es/noticias/bundesliga-divulga-indicados-a-selecao-da-temporada-2223-vote-agora-37328413 |title=Bundesliga divulga indicados à Seleção da Temporada 22/23; vote agora |publisher=OneFootball |language=pt |date=2023-04-27 |access-date=2023-07-28}}</ref>

Lee seemed lethargic while Mainz earned only one win in the first half of the [[2023–24 Bundesliga|2023–24 season]], but he played a key role in saving his team from relegation during the second half of the season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kicker.de/bundesliga-sommer-2024/offensives-mittelfeld/rangliste |title=Rangliste Sommer 2024, Mittelfeld offensiv |language=de |publisher=kicker |access-date=2024-08-05}}</ref>

Lee scored two goals in a 2–1 win over Bayern Munich on 14 December 2024, leading Bayern to their first defeat in the [[2024–25 Bundesliga]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/mainz-bayern-munich-match-report-highlights-matchday-14-kompany-30085 |title=Jae-sung Lee double inflicts first league defeat on Bayern Munich |publisher=Bundesliga |date=2024-12-15 |access-date=2024-12-15}}</ref> During the 2024–25 season, he had seven goals and six assists (ten assists according to the standard of ''kicker'') in 33 league appearances,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/player/jae-sung-lee |title=Jae-sung Lee Stats season 2024-2025 |publisher=Bundesliga |access-date=2025-05-24}}</ref><ref name="24-25"/> helping Mainz qualify for the [[2025–26 UEFA Conference League]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.mainz05.de/en/news-en/m05b04-match-report-17052025 |title=FSV secure European qualification |publisher=1. FSV Mainz 05 |date=2025-05-17 |access-date=2025-05-24}}</ref>

After coming on as a 60th minute substitute in a [[2025–26 UEFA Conference League league phase|league phase]] match of the 2025–26 Conference League on 6 November 2025, Lee had one assist and the winning goal, converting [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]]'s 1–0 lead into Mainz's 2–1 win. The goal was his first goal at UEFA competitions excluding qualifiers.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaconferenceleague/match/2046341--mainz-vs-fiorentina/ |title=
Mainz vs Fiorentina {{!}} UEFA Conference League 2025/26 |publisher=UEFA |date=2025-11-06 |access-date=2025-11-06}}</ref>

==International career==
In the [[2017 EAFF E-1 Football Championship|2017 EAFF Championship]], Lee led South Korea's title, and was named the Most Valuable Player and the Best Duel Player.<ref name="17EAFF"/>

Lee was named in [[South Korea national football team|South Korea]]'s squad for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Revealed: Every World Cup 2018 squad - 23-man & preliminary lists & when will they be announced? |url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb |publisher=Goal |access-date=18 May 2018}}</ref> and played all three games in the group stage. He also participated in the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]], helping South Korea advance to the knockout stage.

On 10 October 2025, he made his 100th international appearance in a friendly match against [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://biz.chosun.com/en/en-sports/2025/10/10/OCNR7E6DRRBLXCSFGPPBBOZUUI/ |title=Lee Jae-sung reaches 100 A-match milestone for South Korea |publisher=Chosun Biz |date=10 October 2025 }}</ref>

== Style of play ==
Lee possessed the ball for a short time, and showed great influence when moving without the ball. He preferred passing in a fast tempo to carrying, and had a high work rate to preoccupy suitable spots. His movement was also skilled in interceptions when defending.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Lee Jae-sung - Stats & Scout Report {{!}} Mainz 05 |url=https://scoutingstats.ai/player/lee-jae-sung-2690/ |access-date=2024-11-11 |website=ScoutingStats.AI}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fotmob.com/en/players/523749/jae-sung-lee |title=Jae-sung Lee |publisher=FotMob |access-date=2024-12-15}}</ref>

